headline: Digi Power X (TSXV:DGX) Is Up 12.2% After US$20M NVIDIA GPU Bet For AI Cloud Push
summary: Digi Power X Inc. recently agreed to purchase about US$20,000,000 of next-generation NVIDIA B300 GPUs from Supermicro for deployment in its Tier III AI data centers and integration into its NeoCloudz GPU-as-a-Service platform, with initial customer availability targeted for March 2026. This step highlights Digi Power X’s push to build an AI computing services business, aiming to generate recurring infrastructure revenues from enterprise, startup, and research users. headline: Review & Preview: The Smaller the Better
summary: Corporate earnings offered some bright spots this week, but ultimately the start of fourth-quarter reporting season wasn’t enough to push stocks into positive territory.  The major indexes slipped Friday, finishing the week in negative territory—with one exception.  The S&P 500 and Nasdaq Composite finished the week down 0.4% and 0.7%, respectively.
